H0.text: What was the name of the German airship that burst into flames at its moorings in New Jersey in 1937. Graf Zeppelin

H1.text: What was the name of the German airship that burst into flames at its moorings in New Jersey in 1937. Hindenburg's Sister Ship

H2.text: What was the name of the German airship that burst into flames at its moorings in New Jersey in 1937. Zeppelin LZ127

H3.text: What was the name of the German airship that burst into flames at its moorings in New Jersey in 1937. LZ129

A4.text: The airship burst into flames on May 6, 1937, while attempting to land at Lakehurst Naval Air Station.

A5.text: The LZ 127 Graf Zeppelin was used for commercial passenger flights to South America from 1935 to 1937.
